---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="How I Read: A Practical Reading Philosophy | Jevan Goldsmith"
  description="Notes on reading for judgment, taste, decision-making, and a better personal operating system."
  canonical="https://jevangoldsmith.com/reading-philosophy.html"
  bodyClass="nav-compact"
>
  <style slot="head" is:inline set:html={`
    /* Match the navbar's container padding so the page-header and main
       content go edge-to-edge with the logo and the hamburger. */
    .page-header .container,
    main.container {
      max-width: none;
      padding: 0 1rem;
    }
    /* The article wrapper has its own max-width + 2rem horizontal
       padding (from legacy CSS). Drop both so the section content
       inherits the main.container's edge-to-edge inset. */
    .reading-philosophy-content {
      max-width: none;
      padding-left: 0;
      padding-right: 0;
    }
    @media (min-width: 769px) {
      .page-header .container,
      main.container {
        padding: 0 3rem;
      }
    }
  `} />
  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>How I Read</h1>
      <p>A practical reading philosophy for judgment, taste, and better decisions.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="container">
    <article class="reading-philosophy-content">
      <section class="philosophy-section">
        <h2>Why I Read</h2>
        <p>I read to build judgment, not to collect trivia. A good book gives me better questions, sharper taste, and a more useful model of how people, markets, systems, and myself actually work.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="philosophy-section">
        <h2>How I Choose Books</h2>
        <p>I choose books by obsession, repeated recommendation, and usefulness. If a book keeps appearing in the footnotes of people I trust, or if it answers a live question in my life, it moves up the pile.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="philosophy-section">
        <h2>How I Read</h2>
        <p>I read with a notebook nearby. The goal is not to finish fast. The goal is to notice the sentence, example, framework, or objection that changes how I would act next time.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="philosophy-section">
        <h2>What I Look For</h2>
        <p>I look for books that survive rereading: clear thinking, lived experience, useful distinctions, and ideas that can be carried into work, relationships, health, money, and attention.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="philosophy-section">
        <h2>Where to Go Next</h2>
        <p>Start with the bookshelf, then follow the reading thread through the books topic hub and Field Notes. That is where the best ideas get turned into usable notes.</p>
        <p><a href="topics/books-reading.html">Explore the books and reading hub</a></p>
      </section>

      <div class="back-to-books">
        <a href="/books.html" class="back-link">&larr; Back to My Book List</a>
      </div>
    </article>

    <section class="field-notes-inline-cta" data-field-notes-inline>
      <p class="archive-kicker">Field Notes</p>
      <h2>Want more notes like this?</h2>
      <p>Field Notes is where I send useful ideas before they become polished essays: books, objects, questions, and experiments worth keeping.</p>
      <a href="field-notes.html" class="btn-primary">Get Field Notes</a>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
